[[San Marino]] is a nation enclaved within [[Italy]]. San Marino recognizes only one official language, [[Italian language|Italian]]. Many Sammarinese people speak [[English language|English]] as a second language and [[French language|French]] as a third.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ethnicity, Language, & Religion of San Marino|url=http://www.safaritheglobe.com/san-marino/culture/ethnicity-language-religion/|website=www.safaritheglobe.com|accessdate=20 November 2016}}</ref>

The vernacular language is the Sammarinese dialect of [[Romagnol dialect|Romagnol]].

