'''Perwîz Cîhanî''' (born 1955), is a [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]] writer and novelist.<ref name="Eroglu">{{cite news|url=http://www.kurdpa.net/kurdi/more/9074|title=Mem û Zîn û şiroveya Perwîz Cîhanî|last=Eroglu|first=Yaşar|date=17 March 2013|publisher=Kurdistan Press Agency|accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref> He was born near [[Khoy]] in northwest of [[Iran]]. Around 1977&ndash;1978, he began writing poems and short stories in Kurdish, and collecting pieces of Kurdish folklore. In 1984, he worked in the Kurdish Radio of [[Urmia]], presenting two cultural programs. During the same period, he was active in the Kurdish journal of ''Sirwe'', where he published several articles. In 1986, due to the content of his radio programs, he was dismissed from his job in radio. He continued working full-time in ''Sirwe'' until he was forced to leave Iran and sought refuge in [[Switzerland]] as a political asylum in 1995. He has worked with several online Kurdish journals such as ''Mehname'', ''Avesta'' and ''Nûdem''.

